<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="256" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1734,1977]" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">
Note: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tindale" authorityYear="1941" box="[223,391,1879,1905]" class="Insecta" family="Hepialidae" genus="Endoclita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chrysoptera">
<emphasis box="[223,391,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">E. chrysoptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected from Senchal Range, Darjeeling which was under the state 
<collectingRegion box="[1251,1332,1879,1905]" country="India" name="Sikkim" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">Sikkim</collectingRegion>
in 1941. 
<bibRefCitation author="Grehan, J. R. &amp; Mielke, C. G. C. &amp; Basu, D. N. &amp; Pawar, U. &amp; Ismavel, V. A. &amp; Rawlins, J. E. &amp; Kunte, K." box="[198,426,1915,1941]" pageId="5" pageNumber="256" pagination="1 - 13" refId="ref8927" refString="Grehan, J. R., Mielke, C. G. C., Basu, D. N., Pawar, U., Ismavel, V. A., Rawlins, J. E. &amp; Kunte, K. (2022) A new species of Endoclita C. &amp; R. Felder, 1874 ghost moth from Karimganj district of Assam, India, with comments on the genus in Northeastern India, and clarification of E. signifer (Walker, 1856) (Lepidoptera: Hepialidae). ZooNova, 16, 1 - 13." type="journal article" year="2022">
Grehan 
<emphasis box="[287,344,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">et al.</emphasis>
(2022)
</bibRefCitation>
mentioned 
<collectingRegion box="[558,639,1915,1941]" country="India" name="Sikkim" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">Sikkim</collectingRegion>
as its distribution. From 1988, as Darjeeling is part of the 
<collectingRegion country="India" name="West Bengal" pageId="5" pageNumber="256">West Bengal state</collectingRegion>
, so the distribution has been corrected accordingly.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
